{"metadata":{"role":"symbol","fragments":[{"text":"class","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"AStar3D","kind":"identifier"}],"navigatorTitle":[{"text":"AStar3D","kind":"identifier"}],"title":"AStar3D","symbolKind":"class","roleHeading":"Class","externalID":"s:10SwiftGodot7AStar3DC","modules":[{"name":"SwiftGodot"}]},"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot"]]},"sections":[],"schemaVersion":{"major":0,"minor":3,"patch":0},"abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"An implementation of A* for finding the shortest path between two vertices on a connected graph in 3D space."}],"topicSections":[{"title":"Instance Methods","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/addPoint(id:position:weightScale:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/arePointsConnected(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/clear()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/connectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/disconnectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getAvailablePointId()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getClosestPoint(toPosition:includeDisabled:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getClosestPositionInSegment(toPosition:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getIdPath(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointCapacity()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointConnections(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointCount()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointIds()","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPath(fromId:toId:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPosition(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointWeightScale(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/hasPoint(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/isPointDisabled(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/removePoint(id:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/reserveSpace(numNodes:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointDisabled(id:disabled:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointPosition(id:position:)","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/setPointWeightScale(id:weightScale:)"]},{"title":"Type Properties","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/godotClassName"]}],"relationshipsSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/RefCounted"],"title":"Inherits From","type":"inheritsFrom","kind":"relationships"},{"kind":"relationships","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/GodotObject","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s23CustomStringConvertibleP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SQ","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/SH","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/s12IdentifiableP","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantRepresentable","doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/VariantStorable"],"title":"Conforms To","type":"conformsTo"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"platforms":["macOS"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"kind":"identifier","text":"AStar3D"}]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"level":2,"text":"Overview","anchor":"overview","type":"heading"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"A* (A star) is a computer algorithm used in pathfinding and graph traversal, the process of plotting short paths among vertices (points), passing through a given set of edges (segments). It enjoys widespread use due to its performance and accuracy. Godot’s A* implementation uses points in 3D space and Euclidean distances by default.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You must add points manually with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/addPoint(id:position:weightScale:)","isActive":true},{"text":" and create segments manually with ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/connectPoints(id:toId:bidirectional:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":". Once done, you can test if there is a path between two points with the "},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/arePointsConnected(id:toId:bidirectional:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" function, get a path containing indices by "},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getIdPath(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true,"type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":", or one containing actual coordinates with "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointPath(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":"."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"It is also possible to use non-Euclidean distances. To do so, create a class that extends ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D","isActive":true},{"text":" and override methods ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":". Both take two indices and return a length, as is shown in the following example."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"type":"text","text":" should return a lower bound of the distance, i.e. "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"_estimate_cost(u, v) <= _compute_cost(u, v)"},{"type":"text","text":". This serves as a hint to the algorithm because the custom "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" might be computation-heavy. If this is not the case, make ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference"},{"type":"text","text":" return the same value as "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" to provide the algorithm with the most accurate information."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"If the default ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" methods are used, or if the supplied ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_estimateCost(fromId:toId:)"},{"text":" method returns a lower bound of the cost, then the paths returned by A* will be the lowest-cost paths. Here, the cost of a path equals the sum of the ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/_computeCost(fromId:toId:)","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" results of all segments in the path multiplied by the ","type":"text"},{"code":"weight_scale","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"s of the endpoints of the respective segments. If the default methods are used and the "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"weight_scale"},{"type":"text","text":"s of all points are set to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"1.0"},{"text":", then this equals the sum of Euclidean distances of all segments in the path.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}],"paths":["\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/astar3d"]}],"kind":"symbol","references":{"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/AStar3D/reserveSpace(numNodes:)":{"fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"kind":"text","text":" "},{"text":"reserveSpace","kind":"identifier"},{"text":"(","kind":"text"},{"text":"numNodes","kind":"externalParam"},{"text":": ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"typeIdentifier","text":"Int","preciseIdentifier":"s:Si"},{"kind":"text","text":")"}],"role":"symbol","abstract":[{"text":"Reserves space internally for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"numNodes"},{"type":"text","text":" points. Useful if you’re adding a known large number of points at once, such as points on a grid. New capacity must be greater or equals to old capacity."}],"url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/astar3d\/reservespace(numnodes:)","type":"topic","title":"reserveSpace(numNodes:)","kind":"symbol","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/reserveSpace(numNodes:)"},"doc://SwiftGodot/documentation/SwiftGodot/AStar3D/getPointCount()":{"type":"topic","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiftgodot\/astar3d\/getpointcount()","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/AStar3D\/getPointCount()","role":"symbol","fragments":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"func"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"t